-- Iran Begins Study to Assess Shale Deposits, Oil Ministry Says
-- B y   N a y l a   R a z z o u k
-- 2012-04-22T14:17:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/iran-begins-study-to-assess-shale-deposits-oil-ministry-says.html
Iran  began a study to assess oil
and gas shale deposits in the country, according to the oil
ministry website.  The studies are due to be completed within four years, the
website said, citing Seyed Mahmoud Mohaddes, exploration
director of the National Iranian Oil Co. Shale formations in
Iran are mainly estimated to contain oil, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
